__PROJECT OVERVIEW__

This project shows how basic cryptographic ideas can be applied to image data.
Each pixel in an image contains RGB values. By applying a mathematical operation to these values, the image becomes visually distorted and unreadable.
Using the same encryption key, the program can reverse the process and recover the original image.
